text:
Will Andrews wrote:

> Hmm, you're right about this. I only put this stuff in /usr/local/share
> because ports can't delete files from homedirs. I am sorry that I forgot to
> add something in to allow you to override $shareDir with (perhaps)
> something in ~/.bkmrk.  Suggestions?

I guess that would be ok.

>> - chdir $outputDir;
>> --my $rootpage     = &readFile("src/rootpage.html");
>> --my $linkspage    = &readFile("src/linkspage.html");
>> --my $contentspage = &readFile("src/contentspage.html") if ($doContents);
>> -+my $shareDir	= '/usr/local/share/bkmrkconv';
>> -+my $rootpage     = &readFile("$shareDir/src/rootpage.html");
>> -+my $linkspage    = &readFile("$shareDir/src/linkspage.html");
>> -+my $contentspage = &readFile("$shareDir/src/contentspage.html") if ($doContents);
>> - chdir $oldcwd;
>> +-    open(INFILE, "<$file") or die "Unable to open $file: $!\n";
>> ++    open(INFILE, "<$file")
>> ++      or open(INFILE, "</usr/local/share/bkmrkconv/$file")
>> ++      or die "Unable to open $file: $!\n";
>> +     while(<INFILE>) { $data .= $_; }
>> +     close(INFILE) or die "Unable to close $file: $!\n";
>>   
>> - my %root;
> 
> Are you sure this patch allows local overriding?

It works fine for me.  If $file exists in the output directory, that
copy is used, otherwise the copy in /usr/local/share/bkmrkconv is used.

